.TH FRAME_CONSUMER 1 "February 2026" "ws-camerad 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
frame_consumer \- access raw video frames from ws-camerad shared memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B frame_consumer
[\fIshm_name\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B frame_consumer
demonstrates reading raw video frames from ws-camerad's shared memory interface.
.PP
Frames are provided in YUV420 or BGR24 format depending on the shared memory
region accessed. This example prints frame metadata and timing statistics.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I shm_name
Shared memory name (default: /ws_camerad_frames)
.SH SHARED MEMORY REGIONS
.TP
.B /ws_camerad_frames
YUV420 format frames
.TP
.B /ws_camerad_frames_bgr
BGR24 format frames (if enabled)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Read YUV frames:
.B frame_consumer /ws_camerad_frames
.TP
Read BGR frames:
.B frame_consumer /ws_camerad_frames_bgr
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ws-camerad (8),
.BR still_client (1),
.BR clip_client (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Camera Daemon Contributors
